                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d522">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.85/12–1945: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Robertson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-22T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 22, 1945—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2049. For General Marshall. Transfer to China of Naval vessels (ReEmbtel 2182,
                    December 19). No action will be taken in Washington. According to War and Navy
                    Departments, General Wedemeyer has no knowledge regarding this matter. War and
                    Navy also have no information, and Navy has so informed Commander Seventh
                    Fleet.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
